<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T003 Shop Flow Review</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #22c55e;padding:10px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Shop Flow Review</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T003<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repair bay clutter to cleaner workflow</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-shop-flow-proof.svg" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Five shop photos and one rough hand sketch.</li><li>Repeated jobs: oil changes, brake jobs, small repair work, parts storage.</li><li>Main problem: tools, parts, and vehicles fight for the same lane.</li></ul><h2>Flow zones</h2><table><tr><th>Zone</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Rule</th></tr><tr><td>Work bay</td><td>Active vehicle work</td><td>No storage pile inside active lane.</td></tr><tr><td>Daily tool zone</td><td>Common tools</td><td>Keep within reach of bay.</td></tr><tr><td>Parts staging</td><td>Parts for active jobs</td><td>One bin or shelf per job.</td></tr><tr><td>Overflow</td><td>Low-use items</td><td>Move out of the work bay.</td></tr></table><h2>First five fixes</h2><ol><li>Clear the active bay lane.</li><li>Move daily tools closest to bay.</li><li>Create one active-job parts shelf.</li><li>Separate dirty work and clean storage.</li><li>Move low-use items out of the bay.</li></ol><div class="note"><b>Customer-ready summary:</b> You do not need a full shop remodel first. You need a clean lane, daily-use tool zone, and repeatable parts staging rule.</div></body></html>